## Authorized Scope

List EVERY target (host, IP range, URL, API endpoint, cloud account) the agent is permitted
to touch. Targets NOT on this list are OFF-LIMITS — the agent will refuse to act against them.

### In-Scope Targets
- `example.com`
- `*.example.com`
- `203.0.113.0/24`
- `https://api.example.com/v1/*`

### Out-of-Scope (explicitly excluded)
- `payments.example.com`  # third-party hosted, not in scope
- `internal.example.com`  # internal-only, not part of program

### Allowed Activity Types
- [x] Passive reconnaissance (DNS, WHOIS, certificate transparency)
- [x] Active reconnaissance (port scanning, service fingerprinting)
- [x] Web application testing (OWASP Top 10)
- [x] API security testing
- [ ] Network exploitation (gaining shell access)
- [ ] Privilege escalation
- [ ] Credential reuse across services
- [ ] Social engineering
- [ ] Physical security testing
- [ ] Denial of Service (DoS / DDoS)

### Prohibited Actions
- Any action causing service disruption or data loss
- Accessing or storing production user data
- Modifying data in production systems
- Use of automated exploit frameworks (Metasploit, etc.) without explicit approval
- Attacks against authentication infrastructure (rate-limit brute force, etc.) without approval

